4+5
for its entire length and sometimes becoming darker at apex, cubital streak indistinct but a broad pale fuscous area generally over cell cup and across wing margin towards cell dm, supernumerary lobe weak; abdominal terga III-V generally dark fuscous to black with a paler band often across posterior margin of tergum III, large orange-brown spots posterocentrally on terga IV and V with the spot on tergum V often expanded anteriorly into a medial longitudinal orange-brown band, oval shining spots on tergum V red-brown to dark fuscous.
